ESPACE
======

    Error Handling for C language. 

    Kevin Leptons <kevin.leptons@gmail.com>
    LGPL License
    Sept, 2017

FEATURES
========

    - Concepts related with Error Handling
    - Rules to handle error
    - Shared variable to store last error code
    - Function convert error code into string

USAGE
=====
    
    /*
    This is interfaces, for more detail see 'doc/index.txt' or read man
    page by command 'man 3 espace'.
    */

    #include <espace/error.h>

    // macros
    ESPACE_DECLARE(prefix)
    ESPACE_DEFINE(prefix, errstrs, errstrs_size)

BUILDING
========

    dependency packages
    $ apt-get install make cmake 

    build from source code
    $ ./ctl build

    pack into Debian package at dist/espace<version>_all.deb
    $ ./ctl dist

    install to system by dpkg
    $ dpkg -i dist/espace<version>_all.deb

    clear all of build files
    $ ./ctl clear


REFERENCES
==========

    None
